    <p>Finally, a complexity score (3) is calculated for all the <italic>k-</italic>mers not matching with any known miRNA canonical seed, and <italic>k</italic>-mers with low complexity scores are filtered out. The formula measures the number of single nucleotides and di-nucleotides, i.e. a <italic>k</italic>-mer containing AAAAAA would be (6 − 6) x 0.5 + 1 × 0.5 = 0.5, whereas ATGCTA would be (6 − 2) × 0.5 + 5 × 0.5 = 4.5. This score is used to filter out low complexity <italic>k</italic>-mers that may return unspecific binding.
